data.description: Simple and outside of town! This is 4666 East Prospect Road in Delroy. “A great home to start a family,” is how the current owners describe this home. But whether you are just starting out or downsizing, this updated rancher is a must consider. As a starter home, you’ll appreciate the great maintenance record and updates, particularly in the kitchen which features laminate flooring and stylish tile backsplash.  The kitchen opens up to a large living room where the current owners did most of their living and spending time with one another as a family.  In addition to two-bedrooms, there is a versatile room that could be utilized as a nursery, third bedroom,  a workspace for remote work or study, or you could alternatively convert it to a laundry room for the convenience of one-level living, an ideal feature for the downsizer. Outside you’ll enjoy ample yard for play and a nice buffer from neighbors compared to in-town living.  Whether it’s gardening, playing with the kids, or simply relaxing outdoors, this yard delivers!  If there is a tinkerer in the family or anyone who simply enjoys shelter for their vehicle as the winter weather comes nearer, this home features a built-in 1-car garage. For the practical mind, one notable feature of this home is its ample storage with a step up attic, & full basement. Say goodbye to clutter and hello to organized living! Living here offers a unique set of amenities for your lifestyle.  If you like to fish or kayak, or if you’re looking for a change of scenery, take a short 10-minute drive to the picturesque Susquehanna River. Many East York amenities such as supermarkets, restaurants, Target & other shopping are also just 10 minutes away for your convenience.  Have a commute or like to get away? I-83 and Route 30 are both around 10 minutes away.
